### Exercise 3: Thread Context Initialization

**Objective:** Complete `init_thread_ctx` function in `kernel/arch/aarch64/sched/context.c` to initialize the thread context for switching from kernel to user mode.

**Code Implementation:**

```c
/* kernel/arch/aarch64/sched/context.c */

void init_thread_ctx(struct thread *thread, vaddr_t stack, vaddr_t func,
                     u32 prio, u32 type, s32 aff)
{
        /* Fill the context of the thread */
        thread->thread_ctx->ec.reg[SP_EL0] = stack;
        thread->thread_ctx->ec.reg[ELR_EL1] = func;
        thread->thread_ctx->ec.reg[SPSR_EL1] = SPSR_EL1_EL0t;

        /* Set the state of the thread */
        thread->thread_ctx->state = TS_INIT;

        /* Set thread type */
        thread->thread_ctx->type = type;

        /* Set the cpuid and affinity */
        thread->thread_ctx->affinity = aff;

        /* Set the budget and priority of the thread */
        if (thread->thread_ctx->sc != NULL) {
                thread->thread_ctx->sc->prio = prio;
                thread->thread_ctx->sc->budget = DEFAULT_BUDGET;
        }

        thread->thread_ctx->kernel_stack_state = KS_FREE;
        /* Set exiting state */
        thread->thread_ctx->thread_exit_state = TE_RUNNING;
        thread->thread_ctx->is_suspended = false;
}
```

**Explanation:**
This function sets up the thread execution context for ARM64 architecture:

1. **SP_EL0 (Stack Pointer_EL0):** Set to the user stack address - when the thread returns to user mode, it will use this stack pointer
2. **ELR_EL1 (Exception Link Register):** Set to the entry function address - on `eret`, the PC will be set to this value, determining where execution starts in user mode
3. **SPSR_EL1 (Saved Program Status Register):** Set to `SPSR_EL1_EL0t` which configures the processor state for user mode (EL0) execution with interrupts enabled
4. **Thread state:** Initialize to `TS_INIT` (initial state)
5. **Thread type:** Set to `TYPE_USER` for user threads
6. **Scheduling:** Set priority and budget for the scheduler
7. **Thread exit state:** Set to `TE_RUNNING` indicating the thread is running

